Subject: mha_bwd: make v3_api_check a pure, side-effect-free dry-run probe

The v3_api_check flag is meant to answer "would the v3 ASM backward run
for this config?" (return 1 = yes, -1 = no) WITHOUT launching any kernel.
The fwd path (mha_fwd.cu) already honors this; the bwd path did not.

Two fixes to csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu:

  1. mha_bwd(): the v2 CK fallback fired whenever the asm path returned
     -1, ignoring v3_api_check. A probe on a v3-unsupported config would
     therefore execute a full v2 CK backward and clobber dq/dk/dv instead
     of reporting -1. Guard the fallback with `&& !a.v3_api_check` so the
     probe stays side-effect-free (mirrors mha_fwd.cu's fallback guard).

  2. fmha_v3_bwd(): the `if(a.v3_api_check) return 1;` sat after all three
     ASM modules were loaded (hipGetDevice + AiterAsmKernel construction +
     .co file loads). Move it up to the config-availability point (right
     after kernel-name resolution), matching the fwd path which returns
     before any module load. The probe no longer touches the driver or
     filesystem.

diff --git a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
--- a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
+++ b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
@@ -229,7 +229,7 @@ float mha_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
         /* drop_seed_offset   */ a.drop_seed_offset,
     };

-    if(asm_ret == -1)
+    if(asm_ret == -1 && !a.v3_api_check)
     {
         return fmha_bwd(traits, ck_args, s);
     }
@@ -353,6 +353,12 @@ float fmha_v3_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
         return -1;
     }

+    // Dry-run availability probe: the config resolves to valid v3 kernels, so report
+    // support without loading kernel modules or touching the driver/filesystem. This
+    // mirrors the fwd path (mha_fwd.cu), which returns before any AiterAsmKernel load.
+    if(a.v3_api_check)
+        return 1;
+
     int ts_odo;
     int ts_kv;
     int ts_dq;
@@ -443,9 +449,6 @@ float fmha_v3_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
     }
 #undef LOCK_IMPL_PTR_MAP

-    if(a.v3_api_check)
-        return 1;
-
     fmha_bwd_odo_args odo_args;

     odo_args.ptr_o           = a.o_ptr;
